    "GPT-2, with 1.5 billion parameters, generated longer and more coherent text sequences, showcasing the ability to adapt to various domains [7,39].",
    "GPT-2's versatility enabled downstream tasks, including text summarization, classification, and question answering [40,41].Building on GPT-2, GPT-3 significantly expanded the parameter count to 175 billion, leading to substantial improvements in text generation accuracy and logical consistency [42].",
    "GPT-3's architecture also introduced transfer learning strategies, where pre-trained models were fine-tuned for specific tasks with minimal labeled data [19].The development of Instruct GPT further advanced GPT models by integrating reinforcement learning with human feedback (RLHF).",
